,{"class":47,"line":686},[45,2054,1324],{"class":55},[45,2056,533],{"class":66},[45,2058,1329],{"class":55},[45,2060,59],{"class":51},[45,2062,166],{"class":66},[45,2064,2066],{"class":47,"line":2065},35,[45,2067,2068],{"class":66},"  createArticle,\n",[45,2070,2072],{"class":47,"line":2071},36,[45,2073,2074],{"class":66},"  getArticleById,\n",[45,2076,2078],{"class":47,"line":2077},37,[45,2079,2080],{"class":66},"  getAllArticles,\n",[45,2082,2084],{"class":47,"line":2083},38,[45,2085,2086],{"class":66},"  updateArticle,\n",[45,2088,2090],{"class":47,"line":2089},39,[45,2091,2092],{"class":66},"  deleteArticle\n",[45,2094,2096],{"class":47,"line":2095},40,[45,2097,2098],{"class":66},"};\n",[12,2100,2101],{},"This makes Controllers — which can otherwise get complex — more concise, and the code becomes more organized and readable.",[725,2103,2104],{},[12,2105,2106,2108],{},[730,2107,732],{},"\nWhen Controllers get too complex, business logic gets extracted into Services. The benefit is the Controller becomes simpler — Controllers focus on handling requests while Services focus on business logic.",[12,2110,2111],{},"The folder structures above are just references. In practice you'll adjust based on your project's needs. If your project isn't complex, don't worry too much about folder structure — these are mainly for code organization and readability, not hard rules.",[12,2113,2114],{},"That's it for this post, see you in the next one.",[20,2116,2118],{"id":2117},"random-thoughts","Random thoughts",[12,2120,2121],{},"Lately my back has been killing me at night. I've tried stretching before bed, working out, and the bed is firm too. After a while it goes back to normal, QQ...",[2123,2124,2125],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .sWyjQ, html code.shiki .sWyjQ{--shiki-default:#FF9492}html pre.shiki code .sCcAr, html code.shiki .sCcAr{--shiki-default:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sj_SG, html code.shiki .sj_SG{--shiki-default:#DBB7FF}html pre.shiki code .sMAXC, html code.shiki 